12 Aug 2016Cabinet will hold its Lekgotla from the 16TH to the 19TH of August 2016 at Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guesthouse in Pretoria.Members of the media will be allowed a brief opportunity to take pictures of Cabinet members. This will be followed by an equally brief engagement with the Minister in the Presidency responsible for Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation and Chairperson of the National Planning Commission , Mr Jeff Radebe. The details of the photo opportunity are: Date: Tuesday, 16 August 2016 Time: 11h30 (arrival 11h00) Venue: Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guesthouse in Pretoria (access through Gate 10) NB: There is an accreditation process for all media attending. Members of the media who have not accredited will not be granted access. Kindly send the confirmation of attendance to Ishmael@gcis.gov.za with details as per the table below. The deadline for submission is 15h00 on Monday, 15th August. To access the venue, you will be required to produce your ID/Passport as well as a Press Card or letter from the Editor. NAME &amp; SURNAME ORGANISATION DESIGNATION ID/PASSPORT NUMBER CONTACT DETAILS Enquiries: Donald Liphoko, GCIS Acting Director-General Contact: 082 901 0766